originalText.text:
Visiting from out of state, I brought my brand new vehicle for them to park. Picked it up the next morning to find my wheels curbed. The valet said they wouldn’t cover it, but said to fill out a form with my contact information.

No response since then. Do not park your car here, they will not treat it properly.

originalText.text: Terrible experience! Awful, awful, awful. Our brand new car came back completely scratched and the manager pretended like it was like that before! Our car is brand new and had absolutely no scratches. He made us fill out a form and said that his insurance wasnt going to cover it. Like what!?!? We were visiting  from out of state (first time visiting NYC) and we left our car here for 4 days only because it was whom our hotel recommended. What upsets us isn't the scratch, it's the fact that they are pretending they didn't do it and not owning up to it. We are waiting on someone from his insurance to contact us but I don't even believe they will. Now I see all the other bad reviews and I just regret having come here.

originalText.text: 24 hrs, so convenient,  ring bell after 10pm to 5am in morning but the staff is great.  Sad that city is making them take less cars, so can't book with the app anymore.  Boo city inspectors...

originalText.text: Attendant was very rude! We arrived early and wouldn’t accept us. As we were exiting the car and putting our stroller together the attendant got into our van with my 7 year old sitting without a seatbelt and moved our van with the doors wide open. It’s unacceptable how he was treating us that we left and didn’t leave our car there! DO NOT GO HERE!!!

originalText.text: They have been great...until now. I have used them a lot over the past two years with no problem. Then I brought in my 1 hr old new car. When I picked up my car the next day, I had a $700 case of curb rash on one of my wheels.  Most of the workers seem great, but now I may not use them again.
